1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel architecture for 1D-CNN to improve time series classification performance, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method involves using a specific design for kernel size configuration to improve the performance of 1D-CNN, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper focuses on time series classification, the proposed method involves using convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision and pattern recognition tasks. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a new architecture for 1D-CNN that involves capturing the proper kernel size during the model learning period, which can be considered as an application of neural computing. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper involves analyzing the impact of kernel size on the performance of 1D-CNN, which can be considered as an application of data structures and algorithms.
